From 36a3827a23d070a68cad09af4857cc3adb6292c8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 21:02:53 +0200
Subject: [slayzone] slayzone: Phase 8.1 automations webui +
 SlayzoneAutomationsHost
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First Phase 8 home-panel port, following the Phase 7 R2 recipe verbatim:

- chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/automations.mojom: AutomationsHost with
  GetSnapshot() => (AutomationsSnapshot) and
  ToggleAutomation(id, enabled) => (AutomationsSnapshot). Mirror of the
  outer packages/shared/mojo-bindings/mojom/automations.mojom.
- slayzone_automations_host.{h,cc}: per-SlayzoneBrowserView Mojo impl.
  GetSnapshot forwards to SidecarClient::Call(automations:get-snapshot);
  ToggleAutomation forwards [id, enabled] as positional params to
  automations:toggle; response dict -> AutomationsSnapshot. base::ListValue
  throughout per patch 0022 hotfix.
- chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_automations_ui.{h,cc}:
  chrome://slayzone-automations/ WebUIController. Uses
  slayzone::ConfigureBundleSource helper (Phase 7 R2) — saves ~100 LoC of
  boilerplate vs the earlier 7.1/7.3/7.9 hosts.
- SlayzoneBrowserView: owns a SlayzoneAutomationsHost; new
  automations_host() accessor.
- ChromeURLHosts() + webui_url_constants: register
  chrome://slayzone-automations/ host + URL constants.
- chrome_browser_interface_binders_webui_parts_desktop: registers
  ForWebUI<SlayzoneAutomationsUI>().Add<AutomationsHost>().
- BUILD.gn: new .cc/.h files wired into browser + ui targets;
  mojom/BUILD.gn adds automations.mojom.

Scope fence for 8.1: dialog-bound actions (create/edit/delete/duplicate/
run) render disabled with a 'Phase 10' tooltip in the JS; the wire contract
keeps only GetSnapshot + ToggleAutomation. Action buttons wire up when the
Phase 10 dialog host lands.
